{
  "texts": [
    "The way of incorporating those signs, however, needs to be selected with caution so the positive and negative contribution scores won't simply cancel each other out hence undermine the importance of the features.",
    "In this study, we assumed that the interactive crosstalk (facilitated by presumably overlapping information) between gene expression and miRNA expression data enabled more efficient multi-omics integration.",
    "The view-specific information (i.e., here we consider each type of omics data as a different view of the samples 13), however, can also be important especially when the overlapping information between different types of omics data is trivial.",
    "Moreover, disentangling view-specific and view-shared aspects of latent features may make the VAE more interpretable.",
    "Models like Deep Probabilistic CCA (DPCCA) 46 might be useful for such disentanglement tasks and combining this approach with our KL-PMVAE for better multi-omics integration and feature extraction is a potential future direction of study."
  ]
}